about.summary: cosinor is a set of simple functions that transforms longitudinal data to estimate the cosinor linear model as described in Tong (1976). Methods are given to summarize the mean, amplitude and acrophase, to predict the mean annual outcome value, and to test the coefficients.

cosinor is a set of simple functions that transforms longitudinal data to estimate the cosinor linear model as described in Tong (1976). Methods are given to summarize the mean, amplitude and acrophase, to predict the mean annual outcome value, and to test the coefficients.

name: r-cosinor
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.2.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-cosinor
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/cosinor_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/cosinor/cosinor_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a0c7e168bee229fa95cc02ea633df53d6bb43c95de8792e533212d7985935e65

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-shiny
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-shiny

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('cosinor')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('cosinor')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://github.com/sachsmc/cosinor
  license: MIT
  summary: cosinor is a set of simple functions that transforms longitudinal data to estimate the cosinor linear model as described in Tong (1976). Methods are given to summarize the mean, amplitude and acrophase, to predict the mean annual outcome value, and to test the coefficients.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
